3 types of SCC captions:
    Roll-Up
    Paint-On
    Pop-On

Commands:
    94ae - Erase Non-displayed(buffer) Memory [ENM]
    942c - Erase Displayed Memory [EDM]
    9420 - Resume Caption Loading [RCL]
    8080 - filler to time out the frames until caption needs to be displayed ??
    97a1, 97a2, 9723 - move 1, 2 or 3 columns - Tab Over command [TO]
    942f - display the buffer on the screen - End Of Caption [EOC]


Pop-On:
    1. 94ae (erase non displayed memory)
    2. 9420 (resume caption loading => this command here means we're using Pop-On captions)
    3. Positioning/ styling command (can position on columns divisible by 4)
        The control chars is called Preamble Address Code [PAC].
    4. If positioning needs to be on columns not divisible by 4, use a [TO] command